fixes z :: complex
assumes h0 : "z = Complex (Re 7) (Im (-24))"
shows  "cmod z = 25"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Evaluate $|7-24i|$. The final Answer is 25
 ### Proof
 We have $|7-24i| = \sqrt{7^2 + (-24)^2} = \boxed{25}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes z :: complex
assumes h0 : "z = Complex (Re 7) (Im (-24))"
shows  "cmod z = 25"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
a_0.informal problem: Find the modulus of the complex number $7 - 24i$. The final answer is $25$.
